pecific, so reading between the lines doesn’t work very well.  The only part that was directed at you, Ela, were the first two sentences: it would better serve your arguments if you stopped comparing assassins to archers (the rest of the post was a statement to everyone regarding general attitude).  I know it is for the sake of illustration, but your points could be illustrated using other classes, or without bringing any other class into the equation, and my immediate impression upon seeing several (all? well, won’t generalize) of your reports is &quot;assassins vs. archers&quot;.  I have personally seen you reply in defense to your own threads &quot;This is NOT a request to nerf archers!&quot; at least three times, so I’m not the only one.<br><br>The previous paragraph stands alone, but allow me to go into more detail.  I assume you welcome critical inquiry.  Your argument, in my perception, is that &quot;even an archer can melee better than an assassin, so Critical Strike should be more powerful&quot;, and your supporting evidence is three main points: archers use superior armor than assassins, archers have buffs that are beneficial to melee combat, weapon skill styles are superior to critical strike styles.<br><br>1. Archers use superior armor. This is one facet of the reason archers are overpowered.  It would make perfect sense for balance if the situation was reversed and assassins used reinforced and archers used leather.  It will never happen.<br><br>2. Archers have buffs that are beneficial to melee combat.  Another facet of archer imbalance: in addition to all their other abilities they have self-buffs.  If archers had this taken away, they would still be too powerful in RvR.  But it also won’t happen.<br><br>1 and 2 are direct comparisons to archers, and therefore weak, in my opinion.  Don’t get me wrong, they are absolutely true, but it’s comparing apples and gold.<br><br>3. Weapon styles are superior to Critical Strike styles.  This point is far more compelling, but the comparison to archers is unnecessary and weakens the argument.  Here you can compare assassins to assassins, or simply styles to styles without mentioning classes at all.  The latter would actually be better, because you could also compare Critical Strike to non-rogue weapon styles such as Large Weaponry and Celtic Spear, without bringing class into the discussion.<br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uvalarauco.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valarauco</A> at: 2/1/02 6:04:38 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucaowyth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caowyth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 2:10:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1983.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ela’s Assassin Volume IV 1/2</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I'm just tired of the whining.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>People used to say the same sort of things about EQ rogues.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uwinderpane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Winderpane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 3:20:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1983.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ela’s Assassin Volume IV 1/2</span><hr size=1> Please continue to compare Archers and Assassins. Class balance does not happen in a vacuum, it happens by creating balance across all classes.<br><br>If only th